---
import { Picture } from "astro:assets";
import HeroImage from "../images/hero.jpeg";
---

<div class="hero">
  <Picture
    src={HeroImage}
    alt="hero image of starling murmuration.  image by bios48 on stock.adobe.com"
    onload="this.style.opacity = 1"
  />
  <div class="col">
    <h1>Participatory moderation in the atmosphere</h1>
    <p>The internet was built to distribute power, not concentrate it.</p>
    <p>The social media giants have complete control of your feed.</p>
    <p>
      Bluesky introduced <a
        href="https://bsky.social/about/blog/3-30-2023-algorithmic-choice"
        >algorithmic choice</a
      > and <a href="https://bsky.social/about/blog/4-13-2023-moderation"
        >composable moderation</a
      > to combat that.
    </p>
    <p>
      PMsky provides a new layer that invites everyone to contribute to shaping
      the social web.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .hero {
    max-width: 100vw;
    max-height: 100vh;
    height: auto;
    width: auto;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .hero picture {
    width: 100%;
    margin-right: 2vw;
    background: url("data:image/bmp;base64,")
      center center / cover no-repeat;
    border-radius: 10px;
  }
  .hero img {
    margin: 0;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 10px;
    box-shadow: var(--nc-bg-3) 0 0 7px;
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 1s ease-in-out;
  }
  .hero h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
  }
  .hero p {
    margin-bottom: 0.4em;
  }
  @media screen and (min-width: 750px) {
    .hero {
      flex-direction: row;
    }
    .hero picture {
      width: 180%;
    }
  }
</style>
